###########################################################################
#  text_currentcolor_default - exercises z53.c's "fold default black to    #
#  currentColor" rule.  The SVG back end emits fill="currentColor" for     #
#  text and stroke="currentColor" for default-black underline rules so     #
#  that a CSS `color:` declaration on the wrapping HTML can re-tint the    #
#  whole document (light/dark mode).  rsvg-convert resolves currentColor   #
#  to black when no inherited color is set, matching the PS reference      #
#  pixel-for-pixel, so the snippet is also a regression check that the     #
#  default-resolution stays black.                                         #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
This paragraph contains only default-coloured text.  The SVG back end
emits each word with fill="currentColor"; the PostScript back end
emits the equivalent setgray 0 (pure black).  Because the SVG default
for currentColor with no CSS cascade is black, the two raster outputs
should be pixel-identical.
@PP
A second paragraph confirms the same currentColor fold applies across
paragraph breaks and that the @PP-driven baseline advance is identical
between the two back ends.
@End @Text
